                <p>Next, we draw a curve through the points, making sure the graph will approach but never reach the <m>x</m>-axis as <m>x\rightarrow \infty</m>.</p>
                <figure xml:id="fig-graph-exp-2-negx-lt-1-complete">
                    <caption>The graph of <m>f(x) = \left( \frac{1}{2} \right)^x</m> and its sample points <m>(-2, 4)</m>, <m>(-1, 2)</m>, <m>(0, 1)</m>, <m>(1, \frac{1}{2})</m>, and <m>(2, \frac{1}{4})</m> are plotted.</caption>
                        <image source="chapter-8/graph-exp-2-negx.png" width="50%" decorative="yes"/>
                </figure>
            </solution>
        </example>
